		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Acid rain</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Acid rain</b> is <a href="/wiki/Rain" title="Rain">rain</a> or any other form of <a href="/wiki/Precipitation_(meteorology)" title="Precipitation (meteorology)">precipitation</a> that is unusually <a href="/wiki/Acid" title="Acid">acidic</a>. It has harmful effects on plants, aquatic animals, and infrastructure. Acid rain is mostly caused by human emissions of <a href="/wiki/Sulfur" title="Sulfur">sulfur</a> and <a href="/wiki/Nitrogen" title="Nitrogen">nitrogen</a> compounds which react in the atmosphere to produce acids. In recent years, many governments have introduced laws to reduce these emissions.</p>
